[{"location":"api/#States","page":"API","title":"States","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"api/","page":"API","title":"API","text":"Modules = [Gensimo.States]\nOrder = [:function, :type]","category":"page"},{"location":"api/#Gensimo.States.distance-Tuple{Gensimo.States.AdminState, Gensimo.States.AdminState}","page":"API","title":"Gensimo.States.distance","text":"Return 'intervention' distance between administrative states (claims).\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#Gensimo.States.distance-Tuple{State, State}","page":"API","title":"Gensimo.States.distance","text":"Return 'intervention' distance between overall states.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"method"},{"location":"api/#Gensimo.States.state","page":"API","title":"Gensimo.States.state","text":"Universal (copy) constructor.\n\n\n\n\n\n","category":"function"},{"location":"#GENSIMO","page":"Overview","title":"GENSIMO","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Overview","title":"Overview","text":"GENeric Social Insurance MOdelling","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Overview","title":"Overview","text":"GENSIMO is a modelling framework written in Julia for the representation, analysis and simulation of social insurance systems.","category":"page"},{"location":"#Modelling-Social-Insurance-Systems","page":"Overview","title":"Modelling Social Insurance Systems","text":"","category":"section"},{"location":"","page":"Overview","title":"Overview","text":"The GENSIMO framework models the dynamics of clients interacting with a particular insurance scheme. Over time, a client may receive several services – typically compensation payments – which are tallied up administratively as part of the client's claim. Some services are granted without much scrutiny, whereas some service requests involve a deliberation between the insurer and the client. In some cases, external parties such as lawyers or medical professionals may be engaged in these deliberations.","category":"page"},{"location":"","page":"Overview","title":"Overview","text":"These dynamics are represented in the GENSIMO framework as a succession of client states interspersed by deliberative processes, where each successive state is the outcome of such a process. ","category":"page"}]
